    753, Integration Feature 1: BackendPort typed fn-field interface BackendPort struct shape
    754, has name field identifying the backend
    755, Integration
    756, passed
    757, has supports_jit_fn field callable as fn-field
    758, has target_triple_fn field callable as fn-field
    759, fn-fields are extracted before calling (chained method workaround)
    760, Integration Feature 2: CompilerServices pipeline container all 9 ports accessible via create_default_services
    761, creates services container without error
    762, has all 9 pipeline stage ports
    763, Integration Feature 2: CompilerServices pipeline container port fn-fields execute noop pipeline steps
    764, lexer tokenize_fn returns empty list for noop
    765, desugarer desugar_fn returns source unchanged for noop
    766, type checker check_fn returns empty errors for noop
    767, module loader resolve_fn returns import name unchanged for noop
    768, Integration Feature 3: Default Field Values (in progress) placeholder feature not yet fully implemented in runtime
    769, struct construction works with explicitly provided values
    770, typed port structs are used with explicit field initialization
    771, Integration Feature 4: trait keyword desugaring trait converts to struct with fn-fields
    772, basic trait header desugars to struct header
    773, fn method desugars to fn-field type
    774, me method desugars to fn-field (mutability stripped)
    775, trait with multiple methods desugars all to fn-fields
    776, Integration Feature 4: trait keyword desugaring impl-for generates factory functions
    777, impl-for generates a factory function name
    778, generated factory returns the trait type
    779, non-trait source passes through unchanged
    780, Integration Feature 5: DI Extensions as plugin point DiContainer as dynamic service registry
    781, can register and resolve a plugin service
    782, can register multiple services
    783, resolve_or returns default when service not registered
    784, has returns false for unregistered service
    785, Integration Feature 5: DI Extensions as plugin point extensions support factory-based bindings
    786, bind registers a factory callable
    787, resolve calls the factory and returns result
    788, Integration Feature 6: Structural Subtyping (in progress) placeholder feature not yet fully implemented
    789, structs with same field names are compatible (placeholder)
    790, typed port structs demonstrate composition over inheritance
    791, Integration Feature 7: Implicit Context Parameters (in progress) placeholder context val with_context not yet implemented
    792, explicit context passing works as current workaround
    793, DI container provides context-like dependency resolution
    794, Integration Feature 8: Architecture validation arch rule pattern matching
    795, matches exact module path
    796, glob matches sub-paths
    797, denies import matching deny pattern
    798, allows import not matching deny pattern
    799, allows import matching allow pattern
    800, Integration Feature 8: Architecture validation arch check runs on project
    801, project source directory is accessible
    802, arch_check source file exists
    803, check-arch command is wired into main CLI
    804, Integration Feature 9: DI Lock explicit lock prevents modifications
    805, is_locked returns false before locking
    806, is_locked returns true after lock()
    807, locked container rejects bind_instance
    808, locked container rejects bind factory
    809, resolve still works when locked
    810, unlock allows new bindings after lock
    811, Integration Feature 9: DI Lock env-var lock (system test protection)
    812, SIMPLE_SYSTEM_TEST=1 blocks bind operations
    813, SIMPLE_DI_TEST=1 bypasses env-var lock
    814, Integration: Full mini-compiler pipeline (all 9 features) simulated compile-a-file scenario
    815, Step 1 2: create typed service container (Features 1 2)
    816, Step 4: desugar trait to struct before parse (Feature 4)
    817, Step 4 2: desugared struct matches port pattern (Features 4 2)
    818, Step 5: register plugin via DI extensions (Feature 5)
    819, Step 5 2: run noop pipeline stages from CompilerServices (Features 5 2)
    820, Step 9: lock DI after setup (Feature 9)
    821, Step 8: verify architecture rules via check_arch (Feature 8)
    822, Pipeline: all port names follow naming convention (Features 1 2)
